  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2329",
  "title": "Always show all categories, even if empty",
  "body": "My current setup looks somewhat like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar search = instantsearch({\r\n        appId: appId,\r\n        apiKey: apiKey,\r\n        indexName: 'kategorien',\r\n        urlSync: false,\r\n        searchParameters: {\r\n                hierarchicalFacetsRefinements: {\r\n                        facet: ['Fehlbildungen']\r\n                }\r\n        }\r\n});\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n        instantsearch.widgets.searchBox({\r\n                container: '#indikationen_search'\r\n        })\r\n);\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n        instantsearch.widgets.menu({\r\n                container: '#categories',\r\n                attributeName: 'facet',\r\n                sortBy: ['name:asc']\r\n        })\r\n);\r\n\r\nsearch.start();\r\n\r\n// reset set filters when typing\r\n$('input#indikationen_search').on('keyup', function(){\r\n        search.helper.clearRefinements();\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nBy default Algolia hides all categories/facet that have no result when I type something, so the categories expand to full width, which looks odd:\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2017-09-12 at 2 27 18 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3603346/30325840-95b9d0c0-97c6-11e7-9f8a-369cc7627b9d.png)\r\n\r\nStandard:\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2017-09-12 at 2 27 10 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3603346/30325850-a688f296-97c6-11e7-8c45-02a694cde858.png)\r\n\r\n**Is it possible to have all categories visible but to disable them (when there are no results within a facet/category), so a user cannot click on them? But they should be visible at all times.**",
